    <p>
        <font size="5">
            The International Collegiate Programming Contest is an algorithmic programming contest for college students.
            Teams of three, representing their university, work to solve the most real-world problems, fostering
            collaboration, creativity, innovation, and the ability to perform under pressure. Through training and
            competition, teams challenge each other to raise the bar on the possible. Quite simply, it is the oldest,
            largest, and most prestigious programming contest in the world.
            <br>
        </font>
    </p>

    <section>
        <h2>Mission and Purpose</h2>
        <h3>Mission</h3>
        <p>
            ICPC aims to provide a platform for university students around the world to showcase their programming and
            problem-solving skills. It promotes teamwork, creativity, and excellence in the field of computer science.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Global Competition:</strong>
                <p>ICPC hosts regional and world finals where teams from universities compete to solve a set of
                    algorithmic
                    problems under a specified time limit.</p>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Team-based Competition:</strong>
                <p>Competitors participate in teams of three students, encouraging collaboration and teamwork.</p>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Algorithmic Problem Solving:</strong>
                <p>The contest emphasizes algorithmic problem solving, testing participants' programming skills and
                    analytical thinking.</p>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Community Building:</strong>
                <p>ICPC fosters a global community of students, coaches, and professionals passionate about competitive
                    programming.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Structure</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Regional Contests:</strong>
                <p>Held worldwide, regional contests serve as qualifiers for the World Finals.</p>
            </li>
            <li><strong>World Finals:</strong>
                <p>Teams that excel in regional contests advance to the prestigious ICPC World Finals, where they
                    compete
                    for top honors.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Impact</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Educational Enhancement:</strong>
                <p>ICPC contributes to the educational experience of participants, offering a challenging and rewarding
                    platform for honing programming skills.</p>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Professional Development:</strong>
                <p>Participation in ICPC is often seen as a valuable experience on the resumes of students pursuing
                    careers
                    in computer science and related fields.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>How to Get Involved</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>University Participation:</strong>
                <p>Universities can register teams to participate in regional contests.</p>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Volunteering:</strong>
                <p>Professionals in the field can contribute as volunteers, helping organize and judge contests.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

